cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.IR. 

The paper presents an algorithm that combines statistical learning models with logic programming to explain the models. This involves the use of Explainable AI tools and High-Utility Itemset Mining (HUIM) problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with classification evaluation metrics, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the use of feature values and their importance as transactions and utilities respectively, points towards cs.DB (Databases) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as possible sub-categories.
